= El retén

The informer network you let grow has a use, and this is it: the Colonel's men now know which roads to sit on. A courier of yours — carrying, this time, more than a courier should ever carry in one trip, because the war is short of couriers — comes around a curve into a checkpoint that was not there yesterday and is there today because someone was paid.

There are seconds here, not minutes. What happens depends on what you built.

- @reten_tragar: The courier eats the codes, talks their way through as a schoolteacher, and prays the cover holds.
- @reten_fuerza: The escort was close — shoot through it, take the loss, keep the cargo out of the file.
- @reten_soborno: There is cash in the vehicle. Some checkpoints have a price; find out if this is one.

@reten_tragar
go-to: post_event
on-arrival: {!
var _roll = Q.inteligencia*0.5 + Q.moral_columnas*0.2 - Q.coronel_red*0.4 + (Math.random()*50 - 22);
if (_roll >= 8) { Q.inteligencia += 1; }
else { Q.presos += 2; Q.expediente += 6; Q.coronel_red += 3; Q.moral_columnas -= 4; Q.inteligencia -= 3; }
Q.op_res = _roll >= 8 ? 1 : 0;
!}

[? if op_res = 1 : The papers are good — the responsable urbana's people make good papers — and the soldier is bored and the schoolteacher story is dull enough to be true. The car goes through. Whatever it was carrying is still yours, and the courier does not stop shaking until the next town. ?]

[? if op_res = 0 : The soldier is not bored; he is the one they placed there for exactly this. The cover cracks under an ordinary question, and the courier joins the ranks of the held with the cargo spread on the hood as evidence. The network the courier knew must now be assumed burned, which is the expensive part — not the person, the map in the person's head. ?]

- @root: Continue.

