else { Q.funds -= 2; Q.presos += 1; Q.expediente += 5; Q.coronel_red += 2; }
if (Q.funds < 0) { Q.funds = 0; }
Q.op_res = _roll >= 10 ? 1 : 0;
!}

[? if op_res = 1 : Every checkpoint has a price and this soldier's is a month's wage, paid with the fatalism of a man who knows his colonel skims worse. The car goes through; a name is quietly added to your ledger of the purchasable, which in this war is a kind of asset. Corruption, the state's own solvent, dissolving briefly in your favor. ?]

[? if op_res = 0 : This one is not for sale — or is, and takes the money, and arrests the courier anyway, because his colonel pays better for guerrillas than you pay for passage. The oldest lesson about bribing the enemy's men: you are bidding against the enemy, and the enemy has the treasury. ?]

- @root: Continue.

