= El Coronel, al alcance

The vanity was the crack, as vanities are. The man who gives anonymous interviews boasting of his methods also keeps appointments — a mistress in Acapulco, a favorite restaurant, a Sunday drive he has taken too many times. Months of reading him have produced the thing that seemed impossible the day he arrived: a window. The hunter, briefly, in the sights.

It is not a small decision. Kill a colonel and the state does not mourn a policy, it avenges a man — the reprisal will be biblical. But leave him, and the map he is building inside your zones will one day be complete, and completion means the end.

- @coronel_matar: Take the shot. End the campaign by ending the campaigner, and brace for the whirlwind.
- @coronel_exponer: Not a bullet — a scandal. Give the interviews and the flight logs to the press; kill the career, not the man.
- @coronel_perdonar: Let it pass. A dead colonel is a martyr and a live scandal is better; the window will come again, or it won't.

@coronel_matar
go-to: post_event
choose-if: parque >= 3 and moral_columnas >= 55
unavailable-subtitle: An operation against a protected target needs materiel (3 parque) and columns at high morale.
on-arrival: {!
Q.parque -= 3;
var _roll = Q.inteligencia*0.6 + Q.moral_columnas*0.3 + 12 + (Math.random()*50 - 22);
if (_roll >= 30) { Q.coronel_activo = 0; Q.coronel_red = 0; Q.coronel_muerto = 1; Q.guerrilla_meter += 10; Q.moral_columnas += 20; Q.represion += 12; Q.expediente += 12; Q.memorial += 2; }
else if (_roll >= 8) { Q.coronel_herido = 1; Q.coronel_red -= 15; Q.guerrilla_meter += 4; Q.represion += 10; Q.expediente += 10; Q.memorial += 3; }
else { Q.moral_columnas -= 14; Q.memorial += 4; Q.presos += 3; Q.represion += 12; Q.coronel_red += 6; }
Q.op_res = _roll >= 30 ? 2 : (_roll >= 8 ? 1 : 0);
!}

[? if op_res = 2 : The Sunday drive ends on a road the war chose. The Colonel is dead, the campaign decapitated, the informer network he built worthless without the hand that ran it — and for one week the sierra celebrates a thing it had stopped believing possible, that the hunter, too, is mortal. Then the reprisal comes, exactly as promised, and the villages pay in the coin the state always makes them pay. It was worth it. It was terrible. Both are true, and will be argued forever. ?]

[? if op_res = 1 : The shot connects and does not kill — the Colonel survives, scarred and enraged, and the war has now done the one thing worse than missing: wounded a proud man who runs a dirty war and given him a personal reason. The network staggers; the reprisal is immediate; and the campaign, which was patient, becomes something else. ?]

[? if op_res = 0 : The window was watched from the other side too. What was meant to be an ambush becomes a massacre of the ambushers, the Colonel untouched and now aware exactly how close you got and how you knew — which burns the sources that told you. The worst outcome: he lives, he learns, and he is angry. ?]

- @root: Count the cost. Continue.

@coronel_exponer
go-to: post_event
on-arrival: {!
Q.coronel_red -= 12; Q.legitimidad_regimen -= 4; Q.coronel_herido = 1; Q.political_capital += 2; Q.expediente += 3;
// exposure can end him bloodlessly if the archive is deep
if (Q.memorial >= 6 && Math.random() > 0.4) { Q.coronel_activo = 0; Q.coronel_red = 0; Q.coronel_removido = 1; }
!}

[? if coronel_removido = 1 : The dossier is too complete to bury: the flight logs, the airbase, the interviews matched to the man by his own vanity, published where the foreign press will carry it back in. The regime does what regimes do with an embarrassment it cannot deny — it does not punish him, it *transfers* him, to an attaché post in a country with good beaches, the dirty war's version of a medal. The campaign loses its author. The next colonel starts from zero, and knows he is being watched. ?]

[? if coronel_removido = 0 : The scandal runs and wounds without killing: the Colonel's name is now known abroad, his methods documented, his future ceiling lowered — but the regime protects its instruments, and he keeps the command with a grievance and a point to prove. You have made the hunter famous. Whether that slows him or feeds him, the next year decides. ?]

- @root: Continue.

@coronel_perdonar
go-to: post_event
on-arrival: moral_columnas -= 4; coronel_red += 3; inteligencia += 2

The window closes unused. The argument for it is sound — a martyr is worth more to the state than a colonel, the reprisal would fall on the villages, the war is not served by revenge — and the argument will not survive contact with the next barrida, when the columns remember that the man directing it was once, for an afternoon, in the sights, and let go. Prudence has a cost that is only ever billed later, and always to someone else.

- @root: Continue.
